Interface Node

    public interface Node

      • getName

        String getName()
        Returns:
        the device name; this should uniquely identify the device. On an NDN-capable device, this will equal the device's routable prefix.

      • getDefaultUri

        URI getDefaultUri()
        Returns:
        the device name with the default transport scheme (e.g. ndn) applied; this is for use as a base URI for channel creation

      • loadAndStartModules

        CompletableFuture<Collection<Long>> loadAndStartModules(URI moduleUri,
                                                        URI configurationUri)
        Load and start all modules in JAR. Use moduleNameRegex to filter the module names to look for. Example, to only find modules with a name suffix as "_Module" then specify ".*_Module$" in the moduleNameRegex parameter.
        Parameters:
        moduleUri - a URI pointing to the location of a JAR file containing one or more modules
        configurationUri - a URI pointing to a configuration file for the module
        Returns:
        a future to the list of IDs of the running modules

      • openChannel

        <T extends Message> Channel<T> openChannel(URI uri,
                                           Class<T> messageType,
                                           Persistence persistence,
                                           Metadata... metadata)
                                    throws ChannelLifetimeException
        Open an implementation of a channel with the given metadata; what non-included metadata will default to is implementation-specific.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the Message type
        Parameters:
        uri - the unique identifier for the channel, including the scheme to open it (e.g. 'ndn:').
        messageType - a Class instance of the Message: This type should be a descendent of Message. This is necessary for serialization onto the channel.
        persistence - the declared caching/retrieval policy for messages on the channel
        metadata - a list of metadata
        Returns:
        the opened channel
        Throws:
        ChannelLifetimeException - if the channel cannot be opened
